Neighborhood Guides — Cafes, Coffee Shops & Restaurants (Rain-ready picks)
Notes: short reasons focus on covered seating, hot drinks, hearty bowls, decent indoor seating, and parking.

DTLA
- Grand Central Market (vendors: Eggslut, Ramen Hood, G&B Coffee) — communal covered seating and quick hot options.
- Verve Coffee Roasters (Arts District) — airy interiors, innovative drinks like the Missile, signature lattes; excellent for work and socializing.
- Perch LA (rooftop with covered seating options) — cozy cocktails and sweeping views when showers pause.
- Bottega Louie — pastries, warm drinks, and roomy indoor seating; good for made-for-rain days.
- Little Tokyo‑area ramen spots (e.g., Daikokuya) — steam bowls and covered sidewalks for minimal walk time.
- Urth Caffe — classic with comfortable seating, varied menu including full meals, reliable indoor space.
- Cafe Fig — stylish, healthy food options and cozy indoor area, perfect for meetings and remote work.
- Zinc Café & Bar — great for breakfast/lunch, spacious and comfortable for longer indoor stays.

Hollywood
- Musso & Frank Grill — old-school diner with covered entry and long indoor counter.
- G&B Coffee (Hollywood outpost) — excellent espresso, sheltered seating, and quick pastries.
- The Hungry Cat — seafood-forward with indoor seating and heated booths.
- South LA Cafe at the Hollywood Bowl — unique indoor coffee experience just off the main box office.
- Javista Hollywood — known for indoor comfort and solid food menus including bagel sandwiches.

Koreatown
- Café Bora — cozy interiors and hot teas.
- Sun Nong Dan — hearty stews (galbi‑jjim) and indoor booths.
- Stagger Coffee — modern minimalist style, plenty of tables for working or relaxing, good Wi-Fi, fresh pastries.
- Maru Coffee — clean, minimalist design and strong Korean-roasted coffee, perfect for quiet moments.

Westwood
- Hammer Café (onsite at Hammer Museum) — warm drinks, sheltered seating.
- Ministry of Coffee — Australian-style café with a broad menu and spacious indoor seating in Glendon area.
- Bluestone Lane — multiple locations, excellent espresso drinks and healthy bowls, modern décor.
- Coffee Bean & Tea Leaf (local cozy outposts) — quick and dependable stops with covered sidewalk access.

West Hollywood
- Strings of Life — large seating area, all-day menu, welcoming Australian vibe for brunch, coffee, or cocktails; open until 6pm daily.

Miracle Mile / Mid‑Wilshire (incl. LACMA area)
- Ray's & Stark Bar (LACMA) — views sheltered by large windows and hot meals.
- LACMA cafe — light meals and warming drinks.
- The Original Farmer's Market (nearby) — indoor stalls and sheltered seating.

Pasadena
- Jones Coffee Roasters — small indoor seating, quality espresso, bikes parked inside.
- Civil Coffee — downtown Pasadena outpost with warm, social seating and inventive drinks like the Figueroa (espresso, condensed milk, cinnamon).
- Philz Coffee — great indoor seating, customizable coffee blends, comfortable for groups or solo visits.
- Cafe Santorini — warm interiors and parking nearby.
- Mi Piace (Old Pasadena) — warm pastas and indoor booths.

Eagle Rock
- Comet Over Delphi — big windows and natural light, perfect for watching the storm roll by.


